devdoc.details: The Ownable contract has an owner address, and provides basic authorization control functions, this simplifies the implementation of "user permissions".

constructor.details: The Ownable constructor sets the original `owner` of the contract to the sender account.

returns._0: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

ActiveStake().details: returns number of stake, done by particular wallet .

RewardPercentageChange(uint256,uint256).details: return new days wise staking percentage. owner can change staking _percentage .

TotalProfitedAmt().details: returns total staking wallet profited amount

changeRewardPoolAddress(address).details: This wallet is useful for maintain contract token balance. owner can manage profit distribution using rewardPool address.

returns._0: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.

setRewardToken(uint256).details: set number of token from the RewardPoolAddress

stake(uint256,uint256).details: stake amount for particular duration. parameters : _staketime in days (exp: 30, 90, 180 ,360 )              _stakeamount ( need to set token amount for stake) it will increase activeStake result of particular wallet.

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

unStake(uint256).details: stake amount release. parameters : _stakeid is active stake ids which is getting from activeStake-1               it will decrease activeStake result of particular wallet. result : If unstake happen before time duration it will set 50% penalty on profited amount else it will sent you all stake amount,          to the staking wallet.
